						<summary>

						<p>It states that the son of Kāḻitika Antai, a merchant prince (<hi rend="italic">Kāviti</hi>) of the merchant guild of Veḷaṟai caused this lattice (<hi rend="italic">piṇa</hi>) to be given to Kaṇi-i-nata, the monk. The record may be assigned to c. 4th century B.C. </p>						

